WEBVTT

02:23.586 --> 02:24.628
Mom?

02:25.588 --> 02:26.839
Mom?

02:26.839 --> 02:28.048
Present.

02:28.048 --> 02:29.300
What?

02:29.300 --> 02:31.135
Like when the teacher calls roll call,

02:31.135 --> 02:34.221
you say "present."
Mom is ready, so reportin' to duty.

02:35.431 --> 02:36.765
How come you only have one sock on?

02:36.765 --> 02:38.726
I couldn't find the other one.

02:38.726 --> 02:40.853
You can't go to school like that.

02:47.484 --> 02:50.905
Mom, can Alisa come over Friday
for a sleepover again?

02:50.905 --> 02:52.781
Yeah, if it's okay with her mom, sure.

02:52.781 --> 02:55.784
Sweetie, are we not combing our hair now,

02:55.784 --> 02:58.329
or is this just a new fashion thing
that they got by me?

02:58.329 --> 03:00.789
- I combed it.
- Well,

03:00.789 --> 03:03.000
maybe we have ourselves
a wind tunnel in the house.

03:03.000 --> 03:05.461
Why don't you go back
and comb it again, please?

03:05.461 --> 03:07.296
What kind of mother
will people think I am

03:07.296 --> 03:09.882
if you are a mop-head
and your brother's half sockless?

03:09.882 --> 03:13.260
Alisa said you worry too much
about what other people think.

03:13.260 --> 03:14.470
Excuse me?

03:15.846 --> 03:18.599
Alisa said that?
Now why would she say that?

03:23.354 --> 03:24.813
<i>She's never said that to me.</i>

03:24.813 --> 03:28.025
Well, she must have got it from somebody,
so that leaves Betty.

03:28.025 --> 03:30.653
I've never heard Betty say that.

03:30.653 --> 03:32.655
I know she doesn't like me.

03:32.655 --> 03:35.032
- What are you talking about?
- I get a feelin'.

03:36.408 --> 03:38.410
Betty adores you, Candy.

03:38.410 --> 03:42.206
You think she'd be trusting you
to look after our kids if she--

03:46.418 --> 03:49.880
The feeling you're getting
is just her usual

03:49.880 --> 03:51.674
depression stuff.

03:51.674 --> 03:53.342
Yeah, how is that goin'?

03:55.636 --> 03:57.972
Well, much better, actually.

03:57.972 --> 04:02.309
This Marriage Encounter
was really a miracle.

04:03.811 --> 04:06.897
What exactly do they do there?

04:06.897 --> 04:10.401
Well, mostly get us to talk about
our feelings and--

04:11.318 --> 04:15.656
Well, they're big into
writing everything down in a notebook.

04:15.656 --> 04:17.366
Sounds a little silly.

04:17.366 --> 04:20.369
I know. That's what we thought at first,
too, but it--

04:21.287 --> 04:22.454
it really works.

04:22.454 --> 04:24.415
For the first time
in I don't know how long

04:25.541 --> 04:26.500
we were

04:27.459 --> 04:29.753
unflinchingly honest with each other.

04:29.753 --> 04:33.090
Exactly how unflinchingly honest
could you be, Allan?

04:35.759 --> 04:37.678
Well, except for that.

04:38.929 --> 04:41.348
And it was an issue for me.

04:42.474 --> 04:46.186
Betty would bring up sex
and my lack of interest.

04:47.521 --> 04:48.939
And I'd go quiet.

04:48.939 --> 04:51.316
I couldn't exactly say
I was less interested in sex

04:51.316 --> 04:54.111
because I was having it
with Candy Montgomery.

04:54.111 --> 04:56.405
We finally opened up to each other.

04:56.405 --> 04:58.490
Well, that's good.

04:58.490 --> 05:00.909
I'm glad. So...

05:02.453 --> 05:04.079
where does that leave us?

05:05.456 --> 05:08.917
Well, it doesn't necessarily
change the way I feel about you.

05:11.253 --> 05:13.422
But I do feel strongly

05:13.422 --> 05:20.304
that I should be
giving my full resources to my family.

05:22.181 --> 05:26.226
And my relationship with you
is taking away

05:26.226 --> 05:28.771
some of my emotional availability and

05:30.105 --> 05:33.025
energy and attention
that I could be directing towards

05:34.193 --> 05:37.529
Betty and the kids.

05:39.615 --> 05:41.533
So you don't wanna see me anymore?

05:43.410 --> 05:45.079
I don't know. Yeah.

05:45.079 --> 05:48.707
They said an awful lot of things
at the Encounter but

05:50.250 --> 05:52.169
they never said you couldn't

05:53.337 --> 05:55.089
see someone else.

05:57.341 --> 06:01.804
Allan, you seem to be leaving it up to me,
so I'm just deciding.

06:02.888 --> 06:07.184
I'm not gonna call.
I'm not gonna try to see you.

06:07.184 --> 06:09.895
I won't bother you anymore.

06:13.649 --> 06:14.858
Okay.

06:15.359 --> 06:17.945
Ok-- Wow.

06:17.945 --> 06:21.490
Well, you certainly unleashed
your feelings there.

06:21.490 --> 06:25.285
Well, I'm not sure
how you want me to respond.

06:25.285 --> 06:27.287
Do you remember what you told me?

06:27.746 --> 06:31.458
That the days you spent with me
at the Como,

06:31.458 --> 06:33.544
that they were the only hours
of your week where

06:33.544 --> 06:36.088
you didn't feel responsible
for other people's emotions.

06:37.339 --> 06:40.717
Meaning Betty.
The burden of making her happy.

06:40.717 --> 06:45.264
The burden of keeping her
from being miserable.

06:45.722 --> 06:47.266
Now,

06:47.266 --> 06:49.268
have you ever

06:50.644 --> 06:53.564
felt any responsibility for my emotions?

06:54.857 --> 06:56.608
Do you now?

07:03.240 --> 07:04.491
Candy...

07:07.953 --> 07:09.121
Yeah.

07:12.958 --> 07:13.917
Okay.

07:51.246 --> 07:53.582
You realize that every time
you feel a hole,

07:53.582 --> 07:55.167
you paint the kitchen?

07:55.167 --> 07:56.752
That's not true.

07:57.836 --> 07:59.129
Okay, fine.
Maybe it's a little true,

07:59.129 --> 08:02.174
but also, you know, it is good therapy.

08:02.174 --> 08:04.760
- Well, it looks really good.
- Thank you.

08:05.260 --> 08:08.096
I keep saying
that we should start our own business.

08:08.096 --> 08:11.266
There's a lot of people in Wylie
that are looking to remake their lives,

08:11.266 --> 08:14.102
and some of which would settle
for a spiffier breakfast nook.

08:14.102 --> 08:17.606
You know, it's not even like
I'm gonna miss the sex.

08:17.606 --> 08:19.066
It's the friendship.

08:19.066 --> 08:21.526
Allan's been like my best friend.

08:22.027 --> 08:23.654
Hello?
What about me?

08:23.654 --> 08:26.657
I just wish I could talk like that
with Pat.

08:27.991 --> 08:30.369
Okay, I'm serious.

08:30.369 --> 08:32.913
Why don't we start our own business?

08:32.913 --> 08:35.707
At a minimum, it'll get us out
into other people's kitchens.

08:35.707 --> 08:38.418
That's where the real life
happens anyway, right? Kitchens?

08:38.418 --> 08:40.587
God, I'm feelin' angry.

08:40.587 --> 08:42.714
I don't necessarily want him but

08:43.799 --> 08:45.717
I don't like feeling rejected.

08:47.928 --> 08:50.264
You're gonna have to put that
in the fridge, honey, for it to keep.

08:50.264 --> 08:51.640
Or the garage.

08:51.640 --> 08:55.185
- The garage is nice and cool.
- Why does it have to stay cool?

08:55.185 --> 08:57.312
The weather this warm,
I'm afraid it'll rot,

08:57.312 --> 09:00.607
and we still have two whole weeks
before Halloween.

09:09.199 --> 09:11.576
<i>I think it's just a benign fibrous mass.</i>

09:11.576 --> 09:14.288
You can't possibly know that.
Not for sure.

09:14.288 --> 09:16.790
Betty, this is likely harmless.

09:16.790 --> 09:18.834
How dare you be impatient with me.

09:18.834 --> 09:20.335
It could be cancer.

09:21.420 --> 09:22.963
I don't think it is.

09:22.963 --> 09:24.881
But you can't know that!

09:24.881 --> 09:27.551
I actually can know it.

09:27.551 --> 09:29.720
It's my business to know it.

09:30.470 --> 09:32.514
And the mammogram confirms it.

09:32.514 --> 09:34.057
So it's nothing?

09:34.057 --> 09:38.478
It's a mass, yes.
But it's benign.

09:38.478 --> 09:40.397
You should stop taking birth control

09:41.023 --> 09:43.275
and also control your caffeine intake.

09:43.275 --> 09:45.360
It could be from drinking too much coffee?

09:45.360 --> 09:47.863
Betty, you're fine.

09:49.364 --> 09:51.825
Honey, I'm just saying

09:51.825 --> 09:54.161
that you were Luke Skywalker last year,

09:54.161 --> 09:57.122
and there are other characters
in "Star Wars."

09:57.122 --> 09:59.207
No, he wears a mask
for the other characters.

09:59.207 --> 10:01.752
He gets claustrophobia.

10:01.752 --> 10:03.670
- You puked in your Batman mask!
- Hey.

10:03.670 --> 10:06.673
- No, I didn't!
- Alright! Okay!

10:13.096 --> 10:14.890
Jenny! Wait your turn!

10:14.890 --> 10:16.350
Okay!

10:16.850 --> 10:19.102
Thank you.
Thank you.

10:19.102 --> 10:22.731
- Wait up!
- Ian, stop following me!

11:16.368 --> 11:18.286
- Hello?
-<i>Hey!</i>

11:19.204 --> 11:20.288
Candy?

11:20.789 --> 11:24.167
Sorry. I know I promised that,
that I wouldn't call,

11:24.167 --> 11:27.379
but this is just for some advice.

11:27.379 --> 11:29.464
I'm sorry. Bad manners.

11:31.049 --> 11:32.008
How are you?

11:33.301 --> 11:35.637
I'm good.
Good. How are you?

11:36.179 --> 11:38.181
You don't sound great.

11:38.181 --> 11:41.101
Well, I said good, not great.

11:42.018 --> 11:43.812
What's the matter?

11:43.812 --> 11:46.815
<i>Betty found a lump in her right breast.</i>

11:49.860 --> 11:52.571
She's fine. At least that's what
the doctors are telling her.

11:53.280 --> 11:55.574
She's already been to two.

11:55.574 --> 11:58.368
I'm sure she's looking for a third.

11:58.368 --> 12:01.746
They think it's benign,
but she's a wreck.

12:01.746 --> 12:05.041
Well, I should go over there.
Is she home now?

12:05.459 --> 12:08.170
She is, but you don't have to.

12:08.170 --> 12:11.465
No, I should go check on her.
If it were me--

12:12.299 --> 12:14.217
<i>You're a good friend, Candy.</i>

12:31.693 --> 12:33.945
- Betty.
- Hi!

12:33.945 --> 12:35.947
Hi. I just heard

12:36.740 --> 12:38.658
and I know in my heart

12:40.035 --> 12:42.204
that you're fine.

12:42.204 --> 12:43.622
Thank you.

12:44.498 --> 12:46.082
Thank you so much.

12:46.082 --> 12:49.252
You have nothin' to worry about.

12:49.252 --> 12:51.963
- I hope you're right.
- Hey, now, you listen to me.

12:52.589 --> 12:55.258
Doctors are so scared today
about bein' sued

12:55.258 --> 12:58.053
that if you go to them
with a growth of any kind,

12:58.053 --> 13:00.222
the last thing they're gonna do is say,
"Go home, it's nothin',"

13:00.222 --> 13:04.017
unless they are
pretty damn sure it's nothin'.

13:05.060 --> 13:07.604
I am sure that you're right.

13:09.022 --> 13:10.607
How did you find out?

13:10.607 --> 13:12.442
Allan told me.

13:12.442 --> 13:14.444
- Allan did?
- Yeah, he was concerned.

13:14.444 --> 13:17.572
You know how worried husbands can get.

13:17.572 --> 13:19.824
Oh, wait.
No, I got that wrong.

13:19.824 --> 13:21.409
Husbands never worry enough.

13:22.619 --> 13:24.120
That's it.

13:27.541 --> 13:30.627
Well, you didn't have to drive
all the way down here.

13:31.795 --> 13:34.965
But I cannot tell you how much
it means to me that you did.

13:34.965 --> 13:39.928
These doctors, they think
I am the biggest hypochondriac!

13:39.928 --> 13:41.763
They tell me it's nothing,
convince me it's all in my head,

13:41.763 --> 13:44.641
then write me prescriptions
for anxiety and depression,

13:44.641 --> 13:46.851
of which I'm on a gazillion.

13:46.851 --> 13:49.104
- Hi, honey!
- Hi.

13:49.104 --> 13:51.856
Can you believe
Candy drove all the way down here?

13:51.856 --> 13:54.943
She is just the sweetest.

13:54.943 --> 13:57.737
- You feeling better?
- Yes.

13:59.990 --> 14:03.660
Yes. She helped lasso my runaway brain.

14:06.246 --> 14:09.249
Look at us making you stand out here.

14:09.249 --> 14:10.667
- Come in, come in.
- Oh, no! No, no, no.

14:10.667 --> 14:14.671
I gotta get back and make dinner.
It's Meatball Tuesday.

14:14.671 --> 14:18.675
This is just one of those hug-and-runs,
now that I see that you're fine.

14:18.675 --> 14:20.552
- And you are.
- Yes.

14:21.886 --> 14:22.804
Walk Candy to her car.

14:22.804 --> 14:24.055
- Sure.
- Would you, sweetheart?

14:24.055 --> 14:26.016
Thank you again.

14:26.766 --> 14:27.934
So much.

14:29.394 --> 14:31.438
And let's get the kids together

14:31.438 --> 14:32.981
for some trick-or-treating.

14:32.981 --> 14:35.025
Sure, yeah. Perfect. I'll call you!

14:35.942 --> 14:36.901
Okay.

14:40.322 --> 14:42.657
That is not the same person.

14:42.657 --> 14:45.076
You're saying Marriage Encounter did that?

14:45.076 --> 14:47.912
I'm telling you,
she's like a flower blossoming.

14:47.912 --> 14:50.498
Yeah, and she was actually warm.

14:50.498 --> 14:52.709
Oh, sorry. I didn't mean to--

14:53.752 --> 14:55.503
Yes, you did.

14:55.503 --> 14:57.631
But it's alright.
You're not wrong.

14:58.340 --> 15:01.259
- But now, she's--
- Just like a normal person.

15:04.012 --> 15:07.599
Hey, do you think that Pat and I
should get into Marriage Encounter?

15:07.599 --> 15:09.893
'Cause that's actually why
I called earlier.

15:09.893 --> 15:13.480
- Well, I'm not sure.
- Well, I gotta try somethin'.

15:13.480 --> 15:15.482
He doesn't know how to communicate.

15:17.525 --> 15:20.445
The thing is Marriage Encounter
is definitely not for couples

15:20.445 --> 15:22.947
who are having serious problems.

15:24.407 --> 15:27.869
From what you told me
about your feelings for Pat--

15:27.869 --> 15:30.872
I do love him.

15:31.623 --> 15:33.041
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

15:34.959 --> 15:37.379
But it really--
It worked for you.

15:37.379 --> 15:38.588
So far.

15:39.631 --> 15:40.965
So far, it's really worked.

15:40.965 --> 15:43.760
She insists on doing
the homework every night.

15:43.760 --> 15:46.471
The dialog sessions, the love letters.

15:47.931 --> 15:50.934
She wants to become
a group leader in the area.

15:52.769 --> 15:54.145
Very committed.

15:55.397 --> 15:58.733
- Well, that's good.
- But thank you for checking on her.

15:58.733 --> 16:01.861
Yeah. It was good to see you.

16:01.861 --> 16:04.406
Good to see you, too. Alright.

16:55.039 --> 16:56.207
<i>My pleasure.</i>

16:56.207 --> 16:57.834
<i>You're all very special people.</i>

16:57.834 --> 16:59.502
<i>Thank you. We're coming back.</i>

16:59.502 --> 17:01.337
<i>Oh, well, in that case,
I'll double our insurance.</i>

17:08.803 --> 17:11.264
-<i>Thanks for everything</i>.
<i>- Yes. Wonderful.</i>

17:11.264 --> 17:12.390
<i>So long.</i>

17:13.308 --> 17:14.517
<i>Well, what's your prediction?</i>

17:14.517 --> 17:16.019
<i>Oh, definite marriage.</i>

17:16.978 --> 17:18.605
<i>Think they'll have children?</i>

17:18.605 --> 17:20.106
<i>Whether they want to or not.</i>

17:21.775 --> 17:23.067
Hey.

17:24.652 --> 17:25.653
I was watching that.

17:25.653 --> 17:28.073
Yes, I can see
that you were watching that.

17:28.073 --> 17:30.241
I bet you'd love to be a passenger on
<i>The Love Boat,</i>

17:30.241 --> 17:31.576
wouldn't you, Pat?

17:32.702 --> 17:34.370
Well, guess what?
So would I.

17:36.915 --> 17:39.834
I feel like I'm in trouble.

17:41.294 --> 17:43.087
I don't know why.

17:43.087 --> 17:45.089
I wanna go to Marriage Encounter.

17:46.216 --> 17:47.258
What?

17:47.258 --> 17:50.887
It's not just the Garlingtons.
Allan and Betty.

17:50.887 --> 17:53.932
Betty, I mean,
she's just like a whole new person.

17:53.932 --> 17:56.267
It's a cult though, Candy.

17:56.267 --> 17:58.394
It's not a cult!

17:58.978 --> 18:00.480
And even if it is--

18:01.397 --> 18:03.107
Why are we here, Pat?

18:04.108 --> 18:06.528
And I don't mean on the sofa.
I mean

18:07.487 --> 18:08.696
on Earth.

18:08.696 --> 18:10.698
- Yeah.
- Why are we here?

18:14.994 --> 18:16.830
That's a huge question, Candy.

18:16.830 --> 18:19.791
And I'd like an answer.
Your answer.

18:21.417 --> 18:22.836
Well, I mean

18:25.296 --> 18:26.631
why is a tree here?

18:27.674 --> 18:28.550
What?

18:28.550 --> 18:31.845
You know how I hate you answering
my questions with questions.

18:31.845 --> 18:33.972
- Yeah, I have--
- Why is a tree here?

18:33.972 --> 18:36.474
- Seriously?
- Look, Candy.

18:36.474 --> 18:38.685
I'm not going to have this

18:39.269 --> 18:40.687
cosmic grasp

18:40.687 --> 18:43.314
that you're looking for, I think, but

18:44.315 --> 18:47.318
a tree, it grows its roots.

18:47.318 --> 18:49.571
It sprouts fruit.

18:50.738 --> 18:54.159
The fruit spreads its seeds,
and then more trees grow,

18:54.159 --> 18:56.828
and it goes on and on like that.

18:56.828 --> 18:59.747
And I don't think we're much different,
you know?

18:59.747 --> 19:02.667
We grow our roots.
We raise our kids.

19:03.835 --> 19:06.462
I think that's a good reason to be here.

19:07.046 --> 19:08.339
Or anywhere.

19:09.465 --> 19:11.551
Well, what's your answer?

19:11.551 --> 19:13.970
Why are you here?

19:17.724 --> 19:19.142
I don't know.

19:26.441 --> 19:27.859
You know

19:29.736 --> 19:31.070
you always want more.

19:32.071 --> 19:34.949
You do, Candy.
Whatever you have,

19:34.949 --> 19:36.659
- you always want more.
- Yes, I do.

19:36.659 --> 19:38.870
I do want more.

19:38.870 --> 19:40.914
And I'm not gonna apologize for it.

19:40.914 --> 19:44.667
I want more from me.
From you. From us.

19:46.628 --> 19:48.296
You want to go to Marriage Encounter?

19:52.759 --> 19:54.886
Okay. Let's go.

19:59.682 --> 20:05.229
So he has agreed,
and we're gonna just give it a try.

20:05.229 --> 20:08.983
- This is great.
- Well, you know, it's hopeful,

20:08.983 --> 20:12.487
and every day should have a sprinkle
of hope in it, so.

20:12.487 --> 20:15.114
You should put that
in one of your Sunday parables.

20:15.114 --> 20:16.699
"Every day should have
a sprinkle of hope."

20:16.699 --> 20:17.742
That is lovely.

20:17.742 --> 20:19.577
And you know what else?

20:19.577 --> 20:21.412
And this could be the best part of all.

20:21.412 --> 20:23.623
Just that Pat is willing to try,

20:23.623 --> 20:25.416
I don't find myself
thinking of Allan as much.

20:25.416 --> 20:27.585
And when I do,
the first thing that comes to my mind

20:27.585 --> 20:29.629
is that his eyes are too close together.

20:29.629 --> 20:31.631
That's what I've been sayin'.

20:32.382 --> 20:34.842
Here's my new mantra.

20:34.842 --> 20:38.930
It's called, "rediscover me."

20:38.930 --> 20:42.183
With my marriage, with our new business.

20:42.183 --> 20:44.978
And I thought of the perfect name already.

20:44.978 --> 20:46.813
The Covergirls.

20:46.813 --> 20:48.982
- The Covergirls.
- It's what we do, right?

20:48.982 --> 20:52.318
I paint, you wallpaper.
The Covergirls.

20:52.318 --> 20:54.195
I love it.
"We got you covered."

20:54.195 --> 20:55.405
Yes.

20:56.572 --> 21:00.868
And thank you,
Sherry girl, for covering me.

21:08.251 --> 21:10.753
So that's 10 windows, and price per.

21:10.753 --> 21:13.214
Plus saving time on construction, right?

21:19.345 --> 21:23.766
Don Crowder!
Church grounds on a weekday?

21:23.766 --> 21:26.394
My, my, whose wrath
have you doth incurred?

21:26.394 --> 21:29.689
Just my normal pillar
and beacon of the community stuff.

21:29.689 --> 21:31.858
Trying to figure out
some budget challenges.

21:31.858 --> 21:34.527
Yeah, buildings and maintenance.
That's why I'm here.

21:35.445 --> 21:36.446
Let's see.

21:38.906 --> 21:40.324
What's this?

21:40.324 --> 21:43.536
Now, if you're serious about
sprucing up the parsonage,

21:43.536 --> 21:44.871
Sherry Cleckler
and I have started

21:44.871 --> 21:47.457
