46:41.241 --> 46:42.867
We have Bible camp graduation,

46:42.867 --> 46:44.619
I have to do my parable,
we have the puppet show,

46:44.619 --> 46:48.122
and then I have five different errands
to run in five different towns.

46:48.122 --> 46:49.374
Hey! No, you don't.

46:50.333 --> 46:51.709
- Three Trees?
- What?

46:51.709 --> 46:53.378
Your parable.
Are you going with Three Trees?

46:53.378 --> 46:55.672
Well, yeah.
Do you think I shouldn't?

46:56.214 --> 46:57.924
No, well, it's my favorite.

46:57.924 --> 46:59.676
Kids'll love it.

46:59.676 --> 47:03.054
Mom, can Alisa go to the movies
with us tonight?

47:04.222 --> 47:06.266
I don't know, honey.
Alisa's mom didn't like it

47:06.266 --> 47:08.560
when we took her to see "Grease."

47:08.560 --> 47:12.272
But she loves "Star Wars."
She wouldn't mind.

47:12.272 --> 47:13.982
She would want me to go.

47:14.482 --> 47:15.733
Oh, sweetheart.

47:15.733 --> 47:17.986
Now, that was just
the most adorable little fib,

47:17.986 --> 47:20.863
but if it is okay with your mom,

47:20.863 --> 47:22.865
we would love to have you.

47:22.865 --> 47:25.326
Pat, are you sure you can't make
the puppet show?

47:25.326 --> 47:28.746
'Cause I saw the rehearsal
and it's gonna be great.

47:29.289 --> 47:31.040
- I wish.
- Okay.

47:34.294 --> 47:37.547
Doesn't that serve you perfectly right?

47:41.884 --> 47:43.970
You can't come back here first?

47:43.970 --> 47:48.891
My flight's at 4:00, honey.
So, with Friday traffic,

47:49.726 --> 47:51.894
I think I probably need to leave
for the airport.

47:51.894 --> 47:54.897
Best to just go straight from the office.

47:57.108 --> 47:59.819
- Just two days, honey. Two days.
- Yes.

47:59.819 --> 48:02.822
Two days can go more quickly
for some than for others.

48:07.869 --> 48:10.288
Then, I'm home, and

48:11.581 --> 48:15.335
we're packing for Switzerland
and we're going to have the best time.

48:19.922 --> 48:22.300
I'm almost two weeks late.

48:26.387 --> 48:28.765
I can't take care of another baby.
I'll break.

48:32.101 --> 48:35.563
- I don't wanna be pregnant again.
- Honey, there's no reason to start--

48:35.563 --> 48:36.939
No, please don't--

48:37.982 --> 48:40.610
Do not handle me. I beg you. Just...

48:43.071 --> 48:44.405
be with me.

48:45.490 --> 48:47.909
Honey, I am. I am with you.

48:49.535 --> 48:50.953
If you are,

48:52.413 --> 48:53.706
we'll deal with it.

48:53.706 --> 48:55.333
We can deal with anything.

48:55.333 --> 48:57.126
Right? We can.

48:58.878 --> 49:00.254
We can.

49:17.397 --> 49:19.440
You wanna say bye?

49:21.317 --> 49:24.445
Bye, Dada. Bye, Daddy. Bye.

49:26.322 --> 49:28.116
Bye, Dada.

49:36.040 --> 49:39.794
<i>"Once upon a time,
there were three trees high up on a hill.</i>

49:40.586 --> 49:43.172
<i>"The biggest tree
used to say to the others,</i>

49:43.172 --> 49:47.719
"'When I grow up,
I want to be made into a big boat.

49:47.719 --> 49:51.848
"The finest ocean liner in the world.'

49:51.848 --> 49:53.391
"But, one day, a group of wood cutters

49:53.391 --> 49:56.185
"came to the hill of the three trees.

49:56.185 --> 49:59.772
"And one of them looked
at the biggest tree and said,

49:59.772 --> 50:03.568
"'This tree looks like it would make
a fine fishing boat.'

50:03.568 --> 50:06.612
"And the big tree cried and cried,

50:06.612 --> 50:08.656
"but the wood cutters cut it down anyway,

50:08.656 --> 50:10.616
"and it became the very boat

50:10.616 --> 50:14.495
that Peter used as his altar
to spread the good news."

50:15.037 --> 50:16.539
Isn't this a wonderful time we're having?

50:16.539 --> 50:18.958
- Yeah!
- Yes?

50:44.108 --> 50:46.736
Hey, Barbara. Let me help you.
I can get the Kool-Aid.

50:47.779 --> 50:49.614
It is gonna be a scorcher today.

50:49.614 --> 50:52.992
Oh, my God,
I just wanna drop and put my feet up.

50:52.992 --> 50:55.745
- Do you ever do that, Candy?
- Well, it won't be today.

50:55.745 --> 50:58.331
The kids all wanna see
the new "Star Wars."

50:58.331 --> 51:00.750
And Jenny wants Alisa
to stay over another night,

51:00.750 --> 51:03.920
which is fine,
but Alisa has her swim lesson today,

51:03.920 --> 51:05.671
so that means I have to drive
all the way to Wylie

51:05.671 --> 51:08.257
to pick up her swimsuit.

51:08.257 --> 51:11.803
I suppose if I do leave soon enough,
then I can swing by the Target

51:11.803 --> 51:14.722
- to get a Father's Day card for Pat.
- Oh my-- Go.

51:14.722 --> 51:17.058
Go. I can do this.

51:17.058 --> 51:18.142
And you better get a move on

51:18.142 --> 51:19.352
if you're gonna make it back
in time for the puppet show.

51:19.352 --> 51:20.770
And I can't miss that.

51:20.770 --> 51:22.772
- Ian made the elephant.
- Bail.

51:24.065 --> 51:26.609
- Hey. Listen to Miss Barbara, okay?
- Okay. Bye, Mom.

51:30.363 --> 51:31.239
Hi!

51:31.239 --> 51:32.657
Hi.

51:37.411 --> 51:40.331
Candy!
I finished with your cassette recorder.

51:40.998 --> 51:42.166
Okay, well, I'll be right back.

51:42.166 --> 51:44.252
I just need to run over to
Betty Gore's and then to Target.

51:44.252 --> 51:45.670
Gotcha. Bye.

51:45.670 --> 51:47.171
Yeah. See you.

52:47.231 --> 52:48.107
Candy.

52:48.107 --> 52:50.401
Sorry. Why call when you can
barge right in, right?

52:51.068 --> 52:52.528
I hope I didn't disturb.

52:52.528 --> 52:55.573
No. No, no, no.
No, I just put the--

52:55.573 --> 52:57.783
put the baby down
and then poured myself a cup of coffee,

52:57.783 --> 53:01.162
getting ready to watch
a little "Phil Donahue."

53:01.162 --> 53:03.164
Sounds like heaven.

53:03.164 --> 53:05.166
- Come in. Join me.
- Okay.

53:06.250 --> 53:07.793
Well, I can't stay long.

53:07.793 --> 53:10.338
Noah's ark is leaving port
within the hour.

53:10.338 --> 53:12.673
But the reason I came is
we're seeing "Star Wars" tonight,

53:12.673 --> 53:14.675
and Alisa wants to come,

53:14.675 --> 53:17.178
and Jenny's just
desperate for her to join.

53:17.178 --> 53:19.889
And I said it was okay with me
if it was okay with you.

53:19.889 --> 53:22.058
Which is to mean
her spending another night.

53:22.892 --> 53:26.187
And I'm happy to take her
to her swim lesson to save you the trip.

53:27.229 --> 53:30.191
No, sure.
That's fine with me.

53:30.191 --> 53:31.901
Well, I thought it would be,

53:31.901 --> 53:34.904
so I just came from Bible school
to pick up her suit.

53:34.904 --> 53:36.906
- You sure you can't stay for coffee?
- No, no. Thank you.

53:38.783 --> 53:41.953
Remember, she doesn't like to
put her face underwater. Alisa.

53:41.953 --> 53:43.329
So, if she does put her face underwater,

53:43.329 --> 53:44.830
be sure to give her
peppermints afterwards.

53:44.830 --> 53:47.041
That's the reward that we have.

53:47.500 --> 53:49.669
- Okay!
- Okay.

53:51.212 --> 53:53.714
I'm just so busy
getting ready for our trip.

53:54.423 --> 53:57.343
- Switzerland! I heard!
- Kansas first.

53:57.343 --> 53:59.720
We're gonna drop the kids and the dogs off
at my parents.

54:00.304 --> 54:01.764
- Dogs?
- Yes.

54:01.764 --> 54:03.516
We got another one.
A puppy, six months old.

54:03.516 --> 54:05.643
He's right out there.

54:05.643 --> 54:08.896
- Oh, my God!
- I know.

54:08.896 --> 54:11.983
What is his name?

54:11.983 --> 54:14.568
- Cheeto.
- Cheeto!

54:14.568 --> 54:17.488
Oh, my gosh.
Your name is Cheeto. Hi.

54:17.488 --> 54:19.490
Alisa can't bear to leave him alone.

54:19.490 --> 54:24.078
Well, I can see why.
You're just the sweetest little boy!

54:24.620 --> 54:27.415
You're a good boy! Yes, you are!

54:27.415 --> 54:29.333
Come, come.
Just sit for a second.

54:30.543 --> 54:31.585
Okay.

54:32.586 --> 54:35.339
- Okay, outside. Outside. Good job.
- Oh, my goodness.

54:47.476 --> 54:49.395
- Nothing?
- No. Thanks.

54:50.730 --> 54:51.731
Well.

55:00.740 --> 55:02.408
Gonna be a scorcher today.

55:02.408 --> 55:04.410
Scorcher.

55:06.162 --> 55:09.206
I almost forgot.
Sherry and I actually incorporated.

55:09.206 --> 55:10.958
We're lining jobs up for the fall,

55:10.958 --> 55:16.005
so if you need any papering
or painting done, here is our card.

55:16.005 --> 55:17.798
The Covergirls.

55:19.133 --> 55:21.427
- It's cute.
- It's so exciting.

55:22.636 --> 55:24.013
Well, I should probably get goin'.

55:24.013 --> 55:28.768
I'm hopin' to swing by Target
and get a Father's Day card for Pat,

55:28.768 --> 55:30.811
so should I just go grab Alisa's suit or--

55:30.811 --> 55:31.729
Candy.

55:34.482 --> 55:36.358
Are you having an affair with Allan?

55:37.026 --> 55:38.194
No.

55:38.944 --> 55:41.322
No, of course not.

55:43.365 --> 55:44.784
But you did.

55:47.119 --> 55:48.120
Didn't you?

55:52.083 --> 55:53.250
Didn't you?

55:57.838 --> 55:59.256
Yes.

56:01.801 --> 56:04.220
But it was a long time ago.

56:11.560 --> 56:13.813
Did Allan tell you?

56:20.945 --> 56:22.363
Can you wait a minute?

57:05.823 --> 57:07.032
Betty?

57:11.912 --> 57:13.330
Betty.
